<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 3:38PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Macon
and west central Jackson Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 337 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Franklin, moving southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Franklin, Burningtown and Cowee.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
